== Bulgur ==

Pour the @water for the bulgur{220%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, stir in half the
@chicken stock paste{10%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{110%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for
~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Beef ==

Heat a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard
any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Prep ==

While the beef cooks, chop the @medium tomato{1}(chopped into 1cm pieces).

Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks and roughly chopped) leaves from
their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Sauce ==

Mix the garlic, @chermoula spice mix{1} and @tomato puree{30%g} into the beef and
cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @pomegranate molasses{15%g}, remaining @chicken stock paste{10%g},
@sugar{1} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until reduced slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if needed.

== Mint Yoghurt ==

Meanwhile, put the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} into a #small bowl{} and add
half the mint.

Season with salt and pepper. Mix together, then set aside.

== Tabbouleh ==

Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{}, then stir through the tomatoes and
remaining mint.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed, then spoon the tabbouleh into bowls.

Top with the sticky spiced beef, a dollop of mint yoghurt and a handful of
@wild rocket{20%g}. Drizzle the rocket with a little @olive oil{} to finish.

Enjoy!